FBIS4-8950 "dreeu076_c_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-076 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 CZECH REPUBLIC EBRD Aid Requested for Industry Restructuring EBRD Aid Requested for Industry Restructuring LD1904155094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1200 GMT 19 Apr 94 LD1904155094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network Czech BFN [Text] The Czech Republic wants the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development [EBRD] to help, in particular in restructuring Czech industry. This was mentioned in today's speech delivered by Czech Finance Minister Ivan Kocarnik at the EBRD conference in St. Petersburg. According to the minister, the Czech Republic has already concluded the first stage of the transition to a market economy. However, the country's economy is now confronted with great posttransformation challenges. The minister also expressed his appreciation of the positive changes that have occurred in the EBRD since Jacques de Larossiere became its director.
